{{notability|Companies|date=January 2016}}
{{Infobox organization |name = The Iran Film Foundation |image = |size = |abbreviation = |motto= |formation = 2014 |type = [[Foundation (nonprofit)|Foundation]], [[Nonprofit Organization]] |headquarters = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]] |location = London, United Kingdom |leader_title = |leader_name = |leader_title2 = Chairman |leader_name2 =[[Manoucher Shahabi]] |leader_title3 = |leader_name3 = |budget = |website ={{URL|www.iranfilmfoundation.org}}
}} The '''Iran Film Foundation''' is a non-political UK unregistered charity with a mission to promote and preserve the cinematic history of the Persian speaking world. The remit of the Foundation is specific and is only related to cinematic history, television history and the moving image. The Foundation covers the late nineteenth century to the present day.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Home|url = http://iranfilmfoundation.org/|website = iranfilmfoundation.org|access-date = 2016-01-25}}</ref>
The Foundation achieves its objectives by organising and supporting lectures, cultural events and conferences, for archivists, and by supporting publications and museum programs.
The Foundation is funded by contributions from trustees and patrons and by various fund-raising events. The Foundation does not accept financial support from any Government, Semi-Government organisations or lobbying groups. The IFF is governed by a body of trustees supported by a Film and Moving Image Committee.
== History ==
The organizers of the Foundation have contributed to the Iranian film industry during the past ten years prior to the formal founding of group.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Berlin "Taiwan Night" shadow people gathered in a smooth and successful - News News|url = http://www.like-news.us/?i116494-Berlin-Taiwan-Night-shadow-people-gathered-in-a-smooth-and-successful|website = www.like-news.us|access-date = 2016-01-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Standstill in development of Iran’s national film: secretary of Iran’s short-length film festival|url = http://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/politics/1382537.html|website = Trend|access-date = 2016-01-25|language = en-US}}</ref>
Prior to the formal registration of the organization, the organizers of the foundation worked to build and contribute to publication of several art documentaries in both the English language and [[Persian language|Persian]].
The Foundation has also offered some of its catalogue to large organizations based in Europe for the dissemination of historical archive footage in 2014, notably the recent Iran history series at universities in the United Kingdom.
In 2015, members of the moving image committee contributed to the [[Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin Film Festival]] with supporting the distribution of Iranian cinematography through access deals.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Berlin Film Festival: The Match Factory Represents Three Competition, Three Panorama Films (EXCLUSIVE)|url = https://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/berlin-film-festival-the-match-factory-competition-1201686132/|website = Variety|access-date = 2016-01-25|language = en-US|first = Leo|last = Barraclough}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Iranian drama competes in Berlin International Film Festival 2016 - Film - Arts & Culture - Ahram Online|url = http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/5/32/180751/Arts--Culture/Film/Iranian-drama-competes-in-Berlin-International-Fil.aspx|website = english.ahram.org.eg|access-date = 2016-01-25}}</ref>
